name: Canis lupus occidentalis
description:
Every year during the third full week of October it's Wolf Awareness Week. To celebrate we're introducing you to the wolf species and subspecies found throughout North America.

Common Name: Northwestern Wolf
Latin Name: Canis lupus occidentalis
Location: Northern Rocky Mountains of United States and Canada

The Northwestern wolf is the largest of the gray wolf subspecies, and is the subspecies that was reintroduced into Yellowstone National Park in 1995.
